Vice President Joe Biden called Iraqi Prime Minister-designate Haider al-Abadi to congratulate him on his nomination to form a new government in Iraq. They discussed the need for a broad-based, inclusive government that can counter the threat of the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) and improve the future for all Iraqis. Biden expressed President Obama's commitment to support the new government, particularly in its fight against ISIL. They also discussed activating the bilateral Strategic Framework Agreement in various areas, including economics, diplomacy, and security. The Prime Minister-designate thanked Biden for the call and they agreed to stay in regular communication during the government formation process.